      "writtenOn": "2021-04-09T20:04:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Speaking of which, we are currently missing the msaa bool on the bound RT tracking, right? I don\u0027t think this breaks anything in this CL since a given RT can only be sampled or not, but we\u0027ll obviously need that tracking soon.\n\nBut yeah looking more I don\u0027t think for GL it is that easy to immediately switch to using some FBO/wrapper thing in GrGLOpsRenderPass instead of the GrRT. GrGLGpu uses the GrRT in a lot places below the GrGLOpsRenderPass. I think we\u0027ll need to keep using the GrRT + msaa bool in the short term until we can switch over GrGLRT to holding GrAttachments. However, I still stand by the comment in the follow on CL that the useMSAA bool should not go further than GrGpu::getOpsRenderPass in any of the other backends.",
